### =========================================================
### 5. Normal CRUDQ Create Employee - Success Test
### This should generate employeeCode automatically
### This should NOT assign laptop automatically
### This should NOT assign default skill automatically
### =========================================================

### Create Employee - Valid Normal CRUDQ Create
POST {{baseUrl}}/Employees
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Ravi Normal",
  "email": "ravi.normal@company.com",
  "designation": "Developer",
  "salary": 45000,
  "department_ID": "11111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111"
}


### Verify Employees After Normal Create
GET {{baseUrl}}/Employees?$expand=department,laptop,skillAssignments($expand=skill)


### =========================================================
### 6. Salary Category Virtual Field Test
### This will trigger after READ Employees handler
### =========================================================

### Read Employees and Verify salaryCategory
GET {{baseUrl}}/Employees


### Create LOW Salary Category Employee
POST {{baseUrl}}/Employees
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Low Category Employee",
  "email": "low.category@company.com",
  "designation": "Consultant",
  "salary": 40000,
  "department_ID": "11111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111"
}


### Create MEDIUM Salary Category Employee
POST {{baseUrl}}/Employees
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Medium Category Employee",
