### Verify Salary Categories
GET {{baseUrl}}/Employees


### =========================================================
### 7. Function - Get Active Employee Count
### This is read-only calculated/reporting operation
### =========================================================

### Get Active Employee Count
GET {{baseUrl}}/getEmployeeActiveCount()


### =========================================================
### 8. Function - Get Employee Summary
### Use existing employee ID from seed data
### =========================================================

### Get Employee Summary
GET {{baseUrl}}/getEmployeeSummary(employeeID=e1111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111)


### Get Employee Summary - Invalid Employee ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/getEmployeeSummary(employeeID=99999999-9999-9999-9999-999999999999)


### =========================================================
### 9. Action - Block Employee
### This changes employee status to BLOCKED
### =========================================================

### Block Employee
POST {{baseUrl}}/blockEmployee
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "employeeID": "e2222222-2222-2222-2222-222222222222"
}


### Verify Blocked Employee
GET {{baseUrl}}/Employees(e2222222-2222-2222-2222-222222222222)


### Try Blocking Same Employee Again
POST {{baseUrl}}/blockEmployee
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "employeeID": "e2222222-2222-2222-2222-222222222222"
}


### Block Employee - Invalid Employee ID
POST {{baseUrl}}/blockEmployee
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "employeeID": "99999999-9999-9999-9999-999999999999"
}


### =========================================================
### 10. Action - Onboard Employee
### Business Process:
### 1. Validate employee
### 2. Validate department
### 3. Find available laptop
### 4. Create employee
### 5. Update laptop status as ASSIGNED
### 6. Assign default skill SKILL_CAP
### 7. Return created employee
### =========================================================

### Before Onboarding - Check Available Laptops
GET {{baseUrl}}/CompanyLaptops?$filter=status eq 'AVAILABLE'


### Before Onboarding - Check Skills
GET {{baseUrl}}/Skills


### Onboard Employee - Success
POST {{baseUrl}}/onboardEmployee
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Meena Onboard",
  "email": "meena.onboard@company.com",
  "designation": "Developer",
  "salary": 50000,
  "departmentId": "11111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111"
}


### After Onboarding - Verify Employees with Department, Laptop and Skills
GET {{baseUrl}}/Employees?$expand=department,laptop,skillAssignments($expand=skill)


### After Onboarding - Verify Laptop Status Changed to ASSIGNED
GET {{baseUrl}}/CompanyLaptops


### After Onboarding - Verify Employee Skill Assignment Created
GET {{baseUrl}}/EmployeeSkillAssignments?$expand=employee,skill


